{
  "texts": [
    "DiscussionSince its inception, Impromptu was designed as an external DSL with its own syntax, rather than embedding it as an internal DSL in other another language.",
    "Instead, many other frameworks like DSPy or LangChain are offered as internal DSLs in Python and other languages.",
    "This decision has several consequences on the usability and capabilities of Impromptu.On the one hand, using an external DSL ensures a clear separation between prompts and other elements of the AIbased application (application logic, generative AI system, architecture of the AI pipeline, programming language, …).",
    "This has clear benefits as it separates the goal of the application from the implementation details.",
    "Moreover, this makes it easier to reuse prompt fragments between different parts of an application or even between different applications, and to create reusable prompt libraries for particular domains.An external DSL also facilitates the use of a declarative style for creating prompts, where the user specifies the result to be achieved without focusing on the detailed steps needed."
  ]
}